Commentary Text: Meredith to Dhoni, out Mukesh Choudhary Run Out!! The plan to steal a single come-what-may has clearly backfired here. It was a bumper from Meredith, Dhoni was in two minds and decides to take off after allowing the ball to sail through to the keeper. It could have been a wide, but Ishan Kishan nails the direct hit and catches Mukesh Choudhary well short of the crease. He was slightly slow to take off but never looked like making it. Mukesh Choudhary run out (Ishan Kishan) 4(4) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Kumar Kartikeya to Simarjeet Singh, out Lbw!! Simarjeet Singh has been given out LBW! And he has decided to challenge the call. No bat involved confirms UltraEdge and HawkEye shows three reds. It's crashing into the sticks and that shall be the end of Simarjeet Singh's short stay. Was a nicely tossed up delivery by Kumar Kartikeya, on a length and Simarjeet gets beaten as the ball spins in. Pitching in line, impact in line and hitting the stumps. Dhoni will need to farm the strike well with only two wickets remaining. Simarjeet Singh lbw b Kumar Kartikeya 2(3)
